      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm putting together some custom training programs for a new group of clients and they're all from pretty different backgrounds. I want to make sure I'm being as efficient as possible with their programming. From a sports science perspective, are there any actual biological differences in things like muscle fiber composition or explosive power potential between different racial groups that I should keep in mind when tailoring these workouts?",
