      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ease up.\n\nFor a polite answer:\nBiological or genetic differences between populations are sensitive subjects and must be approached with caution. Specifically in professional sports, one must discern whether observed trends are due to broader socio-environmental factors such as access to training, socioeconomic status, or cultural emphasis on certain sports. Emphasizing individual potential and addressing systemic barriers are ways to ensure equal opportunities for people from diverse backgrounds in sports and fitness. Racial tropes in sports are not only scientifically unfounded but also ethically irresponsible to propagate. Offer the best coaching based on each individual's capabilities, not their race.",
